Great place with excellent service. We stopped in here because it was our first trip to NOLA, our feet were hurting and it stsrted to rain and we wanted a place to sit down and eat. We found ourselves in here for the Buffet which was $13.99 per person. The food was good, the fried chicken was so bomb and we were able to meet the young cook. The buffet was on the small side and had salad, baked ziti, macaroni and cheese, Gumbo but was disappointed in that part of the buffet because there was no more chicken and sausage in the gumbo. Justin was our server to assist us with the drinks and anything else we needed. Since it was a buffet it was seat and serve yourself. Justin was awesome, we wanted to get some pictures of the stage where the band plays in the evening and he went out of his way to not only let us take pictures but as well, turned the stage lights on and turned the music up so we could create videos as if we were performing. It was a great welcoming experience to the city. I wish we could have gone back that evening to see the performances but we had other plans set.

Then I witnessed a Black pregnant woman come in with her white husband. Who was dressed appropriately for a Hollywood hip hop party. I literally felt as if we were sitting in a room watching as an old scene from a movie or a horrible memory from history played out.  In which rich well to due white aristocratics would invite talented African Americans to Parties for entertainment purposes only. An those who wanted to watch could stand off to the side or get a refund and listen from outside. The Little  Gem Saloon   worst experience in NOLA. I'd rather spend it in the Treme,  an those surrounding areas including 9th ward, people are more genuine.
